  "title": "Project Coordinator (Japanese-speaking)",
  "description": "<p><strong>【Job ID: 1424778】</strong></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Plan, prepare, and execute promotional activities to expand the market for Japanese food products.</li><li>Conduct market research to support promotional planning and evaluate market trends.</li><li>Coordinate with external partners such as event organizers, local companies, and vendors to ensure smooth event execution.</li><li>Liaise with internal stakeholders for event planning, approvals, and operational alignment.</li><li>Build and maintain strong networks with food industry partners, influencers, and related stakeholders.</li><li>Manage and update social media platforms to enhance brand visibility.</li><li>Handle internal administrative tasks including approvals, expense processes, and preparation of Japanese-language documents.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Proficiency in Japanese language for liaising with Japanese-speaking clients and stakeholders.</li><li>Strong interest in Japanese cuisine and culture.</li><li>Proficiency in PC applications, including Excel, Word, PowerPoint, and online meeting tools such as Zoom and Microsoft Teams.</li><li>Highly organized and detail-oriented, with the ability to manage schedules and adhere to internal procedures.</li><li>Outgoing, sociable, and positive, with strong interpersonal skills.</li></ul><p>——————————-</p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. However, rest assured that all applications will be updated to our resume bank for future opportunities.</p><p>Please kindly refer to the Privacy Policy of Good Job Creations for your reference: https://goodjobcreations.com.sg/en/privacy-policy/</p><p>EA Personnel Name: Ito (Sherpa) Yurika</p><p>EA Personnel Registration Number: R25159178</p><p>EA License No.: 07C5771</p>",
